      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIME TO PROPHET (5) raced on the speed last start and was beaten a long neck over 1000m at Townsville. Has been in sound form this prep and finds easier company. Draws low and can go one better despite the extra weight. DEVINE FORCE (6) progressed nicely last time out to finish just 0.7 lengths from the winner over 950m at this track (heavy conditions) after being in the firing line throughout. Uses an inside barrier and has strong prospects. ARCTIC BEAR (3) was beaten 0.8 lengths in the same contest. Had to do it the hard way after a slow off. With a better beginning, he should be right in the finish. SINGULAR (1) is back in grade off a 1.5L defeat at Townsville. Just missed here prior at this track and trip and Wiggins sticks. Has claims as well.",
